Proposed law retains present law and additionally authorizes a school board to engage in a
cooperative endeavor with a credit union to operate a credit union branch at a high school.
Provides that any such cooperative endeavor shall provide for the integration of the
operation of the branch into the financial literacy course required by present law and provide
students with the opportunity to obtain the skills, knowledge, and experience necessary to
manage their personal finances and obtain general financial literacy as provided in present
law.
